This Lion's strength and thing for vintage means that he can use a real car for his craft.

As a side note, the one thing she's incapable of in this modern day and age, is taking a 'selfie'. Shame.

description: You can never judge a book by it's cover. Deep down we're all mushy and full of love like Elly the Echidna.

description:
I started thinking about Japanese tradition and Geisha's and how perfect they look when my hungry made the lateral leap to how perfect cupcakes looked as well. 

This is Cupcake Geisha. 

Don't you just want to lick her face. 

From the DreamKind Collection on www.headfirstscribbles.com

Sweet Dreams

name: Pocket Full Of Kittens
description:
Buffalo Head Girl has some issues.

Part of the DreamKind Collection. 

Sweet Dreams, 
x HFS

name: Stationary Fetish Koala
description:
I love stationary. I really love stationary. 

Buying a new pen to scribble with and practise signing my name, over and over and over, getting distracted by the feel of the pen and not scribbling anything genius at all, is a dirty little secret of mine. 

In my mind, each and every pen contains magic ink that will imbue my pen with creativity that in times of scribble blockage i lack. 

Karly the Koala shares my obsession. 

READS: Karly knew her stationary fetish had gone too far when she started sleeping with her favourite felt tip pen under her Egyptian Cotton pillow, so no one could steal it.

name: Bubble Blower
description:
She's more fantastic than the fantastical creature she rides on. 

Bubble girl loves bubble gum, especially the type from Bubble-O-Bill ice creams. That's her favourite. 

From 'DreamKind' Collection

Sweet Dreams, 
x HFS

name: Hopeless Romantic T-Rex
description:
My daughter is obsessed with dinosaurs, especially the T-Rex. 

Her favourite past time is to google T-Rex pictures. It was during such an occasion that i noticed T-Rex is largely only ever 'photographed' in a grumpy pose or roaring. Reinforcing what a big, bad, scary dinosaur it was. 

But what if T-Rex is victim to a reality-tv-like-editing. Really a big softy, full of love and kindness for the world? 

READS: "Tiana was refuting the bad reputation of her species, 
when a friend suggested salsa dancing lessons as
 the perfect ice breaker to help meet people." 
 
Siou Bye 
x HFS

name: Lioncerous With An Identity Crisis
description:
My daughter is obsessed with tea parties and the song I'm a little tea-pot. 

This combined with her recent love of lions and rhinos led to this frankenstein creation. 

READS: Turns out Lewis the Lionocerous had more than one identity crisis due to his new found love of teapots.

Siou bye. 
HFS

name: Angry Rose
description:
Roses are always associated with such nice things like romance and beauty. What if deep down these thorny flowers were actually quite angry? 

From the DreamKind Collection. 

Siou Bye, 
x HFS

name: When She's Away Gorilla
description:
This one is for all the fella's who 'man it up' when their ladies leave them for an evening. 

I've come home many a night to discover an undie clad fella nursing a sore belly from all the junk food (and beer). 

READS: "The minute his lady walked out the door, Greg asserted his position as man of the house by stripping down to his undies, preparing a junk food dinner and watching back-to-back sport"

Siou bye 
HFS x

name: Seagull Face
description:
This is Seagull Face. After a few drinks on a night out, she loves to play the game of dancing roulette that she invented herself. 

This involves her choosing a dance style and beginning to dance before the next track comes on. She reserves the 'Worm' for special occasions. 

From the DreamKind Collection. 

Sweet Dreams, 
HFS x

name: Dragon
description:
A special release today for a dear friend of mine. One of the most brilliant & playful minds i've ever met. 

Just like this Dragon, he has fire and passion in his belly. 

Welcome to the bright-side my friend.

Siou Bye, 
x HFS

name: Inappropriate Kookaburra
description:
When i'm nervous, i laugh. 

It's a really bad habit of mine and tends to act only as a Molotov Cocktail enticing out tempers. 

I was listening to a Kookaburra laugh at 10pm at night when it struck me he may suffer from the same problem. Perhaps his time clock was out, or he woke prematurely from a dream thinking it was morning? Whatever the reason, it seemed inappropriate he was laughing then.  

I started thinking about other inappropriate situations that a Kookaburra could laugh in and after purging all the morbid ones, i settled on the good ole break up situation. 

I included the hamburger phone because, well, everyone should love a hamburger phone. 

READS: "There was nothing funny about breaking up with someone, but dismally Keith was cursed with inappropriately timed nervous laughter."

Siou bye
x HFS

name: A Grizzly Mime
description:
It would kind of suck to be a 'Grizzly' Bear. Imagine if your name was Grumpy Andrew or Bitchy Claire. Hard label to break away from. 

I was scribble dreaming about how a Grizzly Bear would re-brand itself when i thought about a Festival of "Taking the Grizzly out of Grizzly Bear" where bears could prove to humans that deep down they were just big mushy lovers. 

This bear get's it tragically wrong however, opting to perform Opera mime that just makes it look like it's going to eat someone. 

READS: " Gwenda cringed as the last spectator ran off screaming. Opera mime wasn’t the smartest performance choice at the ‘Taking the Grizzly Out of Grizzly Bear” Festival".

Siou Bye
x HFS

name: Ombrophobic Sheep
description:
I found a phobia list a while back. I particularly liked the fear of rain. 

I started thinking about when rain might be a bad thing, and with my daydreamer eyes scanning the backyard, i was reminded of hills hoists and then of woollen jumpers shrinking in the wash and then Sybill sprang to mind. 

READS: "Sybill could pinpoint her ombrophobia to the day she discovered her favourite jumper had shrunk after being washed."

Siou bye. 
HFS
x

name: Beautiful Baby Tarsier
description:
It's that time of year when 'THAT' baby competition in Australia ramps up. Good luck to you all with bubba's entered into the competition. 

I thought it would be quite amusing if a Philippines Tarsier with her "baby goggles on" entered her child into the competition given it looks kinda freaky. 

Hope it amuses you as much as it did me. 



Siou Bye 
x HFS

name: Leo The Lion
description:
Being a Leo i love my Lions. So i decapitated and dehorned Lewis the Lionoceros and turned him into just plain Leo, the Lion. For all the Leo's out there. 

Siou Bye 
x HFS

name: So Frenchy So Frog
description:
I was lucky enough once to end up on the fast train to Paris working as a polaroid photographer for some B-Grade English celebrities (long story). 

The best part about it was wandering around Montematre, the artists quarter, and soaking up all the colour & personalities. C'etait formidable. 
 
I got to thinking about French stereotypes and out sprang a frog who unintentionally embraced them all, except the beret, that's intentional. 

READS: " Yes, his real name is Pierre. Yes, he is French. Yes, he is an ‘Artiste’ from montematre.  The Beret, however, is just for show. 

Siou Bye 
x HFS

name: Backpacking Gap Year Camel
description:
I was wandering around Central Station, Sydney, on the way to work when I saw a bunch of backpackers loitering out the front of one of the many hostels smoking a cigarette. 

I was a backpacker once. I didn't quite manage to adopt the dreadlock uniform that many do, maybe that made me less authentic? Or perhaps more? 

Got me thinking about what animal would have a backpacking spirit and i couldn't go past the camel. This one's donned his dreadlocks and is getting his 'free' on before he enters the workforce. 

READS: "Clive knew that unlike the other ‘glampackers’ the dreadlocks he had primed whilst at uni, made him the real deal. That, and knowing flip-flops should ALWAYS be worn in communal showers.”

Siou Bye 
x HFS

name: Prima Dalmatian
description:
My mum had a Dalmatian called Speckles as a kid. I was thinking about my mum, she's my favourite mum, so i wanted to draw something nice for her. 

Mum also likes that quote "Dance like no one is watching" but i thought it would be more relevant these days to dance in your bedroom like you were on one of the million reality tv shows out there. 

Go have a dance in your bedroom or get the hair brush microphone out. You know you want to. 

READS: " Delilah's ego wouldn't permit her to dance like no one was watching, so she danced like millions of people were watching her on a reality tv show instead"

Siou Bye
HFS x

name: Vintage Hippo
description:
I love typewriters. Sadly i sold mine many years ago but i still dream of buying another one and driving everyone in the house mental with the loud tap tap tapping. zip-ding.

Hennie the hippo also likes everything vintage including typewriters. Maybe she's watched Grease one to many times to be obsessed with spraying letters with perfume. 

READS: " Hennie was crazy about all things Vintage and preferred to send letters to people typed on her typewriter. Love letters, She even sprayed with Grass scented perfume."

Siou Bye 
x HFS

name: Party Camouflage Chameleon
description:
It occurred to me that i hadn't attempted scales on a reptile yet. I won't be drawing hundreds and thousands of little scales for quite some time now. My hand hurts. 

It felt like i was drawing millions of sprinkles. The stuff fairy bread is made of. I got a giggle from the fact that sprinkles would be an amusing thing for a chameleon to camouflage with. Where do sprinkles come out in force? Kids parties of course. Here's the Chameleon desperately trying to escape one.

READS: " Carlos knew his only hope of a 'phantom act' from the kids party, was if he clung to the sprinkles for dear life".

Siou Bye 
HFS x

name: Stock Market Leopard
description:
My Dad loves economics. My dad loves shares. He can handle risk. 
I don't love shares but i love my dad. 

For as long as i can remember he's always had a Fin Review in his hands. It's even classified as an honorary member of our family when we catch up for dinner now. Especially Friday, which is an extra special Fin Review apparently. 

Love you Dad (and your financial review)

READS: " Though he would never outwardly admit such a thing, Fred wished the stock market was as reliable as his spots"

Siou Bye
HFS x

name: Foxy Ladies
description:
It's almost a guarantee that every popular club or pub that i've gone to i'll end up standing in the queue of the 3 cubicle female toilets, listening to the banter and questions around why venues don't install more toilets. 

This is a dedication to all those ladies who have crossed arms, legs and number-of-toilet-whining paths. 

READS: Fiona, who was known for being moody, wished there was a no talking policy as the other foxes echoed the chorus of every pub and club toilet moaning: “Really, You’d think they’d put more girls toilets in.”

Siou bye 
HFS x

name: Swooped Magpie
description:
I remember somewhat fondly, mostly traumatically, walking around with an ice cream container on my head at tennis courts so that Magpie's wouldn't swoop me whilst my parents hit a ball back and forth. 

Now it amuses me that bike riders have those silly spike things protruding from their helmets in an attempt to stop the swoopers giving their hat a tap. 

The tables are turned on this Magpie as he worries about witches on broomsticks. 

READS: "Marvin would rather be labelled delusionally paranoid than find out the hard way that witches on swooping broomsticks really existed"

Siou Bye 
HFS x

name: Possum v squirrel
description:
My friends are married. 

One Aussie, one English. 

After listening to them have the classic vegemite v marmite debate i was inspired to do this. 

READS: "Paula refused to concede Marmite could be an enjoyable option for anyone. Sam was doubly peeved as it was also against his diurnal body clock to be up late having the fight."

Siou bye. 
HFS

name: Pigsty
description:
It amuses me when people do a quick clean before the cleaners arrive. 

The unlikely candidate for a picture, Prue the pig, with her reputation for mess who waved her little hoof in my imagination. 

READS: "Whilst Prue's actions immediately before the cleaner arrived defeated the point of having one, she couldn't bear to have them think she lived in a pigsty" 

Siou bye. 
HFS
x

name: British Bulldog
description:
My friend Foo loves bulldogs. I was transported to the schoolyard game of British Bulldogs we used to play that was guaranteed to end in a bad graze or a black eye.

READS: "Betty reasoned that as it was her breed linked to the game of British Bulldogs, Roller Derby should be a piece of cake."

Siou bye.

An old school friend of mine has 4 lovely little ladies and a husband who is always getting "buy a shotgun" jokes. For all the parents with gorgeous little ladies. 

READS: "4 little girl ducks went out one day, over the hills and far away, mother duck said "your father is going with you", so none of the little ducks brought boyfriends back."

Siou bye x

name: Easy Tiger
description:
Toby the Tiger has anger management issues so for his birthday his sister made him a t-shirt that reminded him not to sweat the small stuff. 

READS: " For this Birthday Toby's sister made him a tshirt that reminded him not to sweat the small stuff."

description:
I've always been a self conscious walker. It sucks because the more i'm aware of it, the more i walk funny. 

I was watching giraffes at the zoo when their gangly legs suggested they may have the same problem. 

READS: " Gavin hated being such a self conscious walker. The more he thought about it, the more it looked as though he was attempting a forward moonwalk on jelly."

Siou bye. 
HFS

name: Horsing Around
description:
I got to thinking about horses when i was on a farm and then the old saying "horsing around" sprang to mind. Then some how my brain made the leap to my career ed advisor giving me a hard time in high school and how Harriet the horse might just have the same attitude as i did. Hence, opting to be a clown to fly in the face of authority.

READS: "It was after her career advisor teacher accused her of "horsing around" that Harriet made up her mind what to do for work experience"

Siou bye. 
HFS
x

name: Head in Sand Ostrich
description:
If you've been on a bus or train recently, you've witnessed the majority of people with their heads in their technology. What animal likes putting it's head in things? The ostrich. Now ecstatic that technology gives him something else to stick his head into. 

READS: " Oliver was thrilled that advances in technology meant his generation no longer had to stick their head in the sand when they felt socially uncomfortable".

Siou bye 
HFS
x

name: Obsessively Clean Cat
description:
We used to cat-sit a craZY kitty called Kiki. Cat's are known for their obsessive self cleaning. Also for their tearing up of toilet paper. Why would cats do this? Because they are using it to close the toilet door behind them when the humans are out of course. 

READS: "As an obsessive self cleaner, Kiki always used toilet paper to close the bathroom door behind her once she'd washed her hands. After all, you never knew where those humans had been".

name: Smelly Skunk Squared
description:
I have a strong nostalgic connection with the smell of dencorub or deep heat cream. It reminds me of watching my dad play football as a really young kid. It also reminds me of having to sit through hours of my dad reminiscing with mates at dinner parties about those glory days. 

READS: "An old Rugby injury had cursed Stewart with smelling like deep heat until his playing days dwindled into just nostalgic stories that would haunt his kids."

Siou bye. 
HFS
x

name: Pack Donkey
description:
I just can't help it. 

It hurts. 

But i'll never stop. 

On a recent trip from the boot of my car when i was laden with grocery bags that were cutting off my circulation and attempting to sever my arms completely. It dawned on me how ridiculous it was that i detested making multiple trips. I'd rather suffer in silent agony like a rabid pack horse, than return the 10 metres again to my car. 

Thoughts ran from pack horse (too literal), to donkey (the ass i was being and this picture unfolded. 

READS: "Call it lunacy, but Desdemona would rather cut off circulation to both her arms, than make 2 trips from the car with the groceries". 

Siou Bye 
HFS x

name: Budgie Smuggling
description:
When i was a kid, and every week in summer if i was 'lucky', Dad would participate in the good ole Aussie tradition of mowing the lawn in his Budgie Smugglers, sneakers and a bonds singlet. 

Bob is also the name of my parents Budgie. 

I still shiver with embarrassment. 

READS: " Behind the billowing curtains that overlooked the front yard, Bob's family were turning Beetroot with embarrassment."

Siou bye. 
HFS
x

name: Migrating Puffin
description:
An interstate love song for all the people who move across the border whether it be state or country. 

This puffin is moving from Sydney to Melbourne. 

READS: " As Pippa prepared to migrate yet again, it occurred to her that whilst every step she had walked in Lizzie Bay was a memory she'd miss, every step in Melbourne would be a new love never missed out on." 

Siou bye.

name: Dancefloor Meerkat
description:
We know a guy who when he is on the dance floor of a club or at a party, he's always got one eye over your shoulder checking out the ladeeez. 

Martino is made in honour of all the dance floor meerkats of the world. 

READS: "Martino the meerkat was known amongst his friends to always be on the lookout for girls over their shoulder at the club."

Siou bye. 
HFS

name: Impatient Turtle
description:
When i've got something to do, i'm not the most patient of people. This is especially the case at traffic lights where i have to stop myself pointlessly tapping the button multiple times like it will somehow get the lights to change sooner if it thinks that more people are waiting. I noticed i was not alone in this behaviour and an impatient turtle sprung to mind in Western Australia. 

READS: "Terrance was in such a rush on his morning run, he impatiently tapped the button at least 6 times"

Siou bye 
HFS x

name: Quadbiking Bunny
description:
Inspired by Farmer Tom Tom from the Te Uri district in NZ and fanging around his property on a quad bike. 

Amazing scenery and lots of mud. 

READS: "Every now and then, when Farmer Tom was out, Ray snuck up to the farm shed and borrowed the quad bike. "

Siou bye.

READS: "Despite the phrase 'Badger to death' having a macabre etymology, Billy was happy to acknowledge he was both a badger by name and on social media."

Siou bye.

Derwent the Deer loves Gone With The Wind and the more than occasional game of chess.

This guy came to me randomly when i was daydreaming about black tie functions and how men always refer to wearing 'monkey suits'.

name: Jackpot Shark
description:
I married a surfer. 

Got talking about how dusk and dawn surfs are really just roulette for the sharks and the image of a shark playing a poker machine sprang to mind. 

READS: " Sherman knew it was only a matter of time before he hit it big."

Siou bye

name: Pan Pipe Panda
description:
Panda's eat bamboo. Bamboo can also be made into pipes. Pan pipes have been considered by some to be naf. That's the thought chain on this one.

READS: "Pandora was impermeable to the jeers and jibes of other Pandas who docilely chewed on bamboo. She alone realised the potential for pan pipe brilliance, and was sure the genre would make a comeback."

Siou bye.

name: Not So Stereotypical Pukeko
description:
On a NZ adventure with my best mate i was introduced to the strange, angry pukeko bird, a lesser known native of NZ. 

Got me thinking about stereotypes which led to 'fush and chups' shop and this angry bird.

READS: "Silly tourists!" Pete the native Pukeko bird grumbled "Always wanting to know if Kevin the Kiwi Bird is around. Thank goodness i'm not such a stereotype." 

Siou bye. 
HFS
x

name: Landing Signal Bee
description:
What would a bee do if it couldn't fly? What job would the rest of the hive give him so he wouldn't be forced into premature retirement? What are the peripheral jobs around flying that he could take up? 

Landing Signal Officers! I've loved them since i saw top gun and i've imagined myself as one from behind the glass of airports many a time.

Thinking of top gun, another favourite thing of mine, i just had to do a tribute to the fly by. "Negative ghost rider, the pattern is full". In this instance the bee is the instigator. 

READS: "After a workplace injury severley limited his own flight time, Bevan amused himself by randomly forcing pollen laden bees into Top Gun Style fly bys of the hive. "

Siou Bye 
x HFS
